Parses URIs and URLs

The following are two example URLs and their component parts::

https://admin:hunter1@example.com:8042/over/there?name=ferret#nose
 \_/   \___/ \_____/ \_________/ \__/\_________/ \_________/ \__/
  |      |       |       |        |       |          |         |
scheme username password hostname port   path      query   fragment

proc paths(url: Url): seq[string] {....raises: [], tags: [], forbids: [].}
Returns the path segments (path split on '/'). This returns the same path segments for both relative and absolute paths. For example: "/" -> @ "" -> @ "/a/b/c" -> @"a", "b", "c" "a/b/c" -> @"a", "b", "c" Source   Edit
